title: Peak Florida: Snake Eating Another Snake Gets Interrupted By An Angry Wasp
text: 1 / 5 Rattlesnake These snakes are commonly found throughout North and South America. They are the largest of the venomous snakes in the United States, according to the CDC. Depending on the species, they can range from one to eight feet. Be careful during hot summer nights when they are most active. They will use their rattles as a warning to you when they feel threatened. Photo Credit: Pixabay Click Here to See The World’s Most Dangerous Snakes
